International arrivals at Greek
airports dropped 3.1 percent in the first eight months of the
year, according to the  Association of Greek Tourism Enterprises .  The number of people arriving from abroad declined to 8.5
million, from 8.8 million in the same period a year earlier, the
Athens-based association said today in a statement on its
website. In August, international arrivals dropped 1 percent to
2.2 million.  The 15 airports covered in the survey account for 95
percent of all arrivals by air from abroad.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Natalie Weeks in Athens at 
